                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12454036" author="fuzzylogic" created="Tue, 28 Nov 2006 17:30:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Part of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-1982&quot; title=&quot;Remove support for JDK 1.3 in 10.3 and onwards&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-1982&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-1982&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12463845" author="knutanders" created="Thu, 11 Jan 2007 09:17:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have attached a patch which makes the java/drda subtree use jdk1.4 libraries under compilation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Description of the patch:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Change source and target level from 1.3 to 1.4 in all build files under java/drda&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Use $
{java14compile.classpath}
&lt;p&gt; instead of $&lt;/p&gt;
{java13compile.classpath}
&lt;p&gt; and $&lt;/p&gt;
{compile.classpath}
&lt;p&gt; in build files under java/drda&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Add $
{j14lib}/jce.jar to java14compile.classpath so that we don&apos;t need to download jce-1.2.2 to compile the network server (but we still need it for other parts of the code)&lt;br/&gt;
* Update building instructions for IBM&apos;s SDK. Now ${j14lib}
&lt;p&gt;/ibmjcefw.jar must be added to java14compile.classpath. (I haven&apos;t tested this myself.)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Clean up the Engine* interfaces. (Some of the JDBC 3.0 methods could be removed from the interfaces, and the network server could in many cases use the JDBC interfaces directly.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Reviews would be appreciated. Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12464149" author="bernt" created="Fri, 12 Jan 2007 10:17:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch seems ok.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12464167" author="knutanders" created="Fri, 12 Jan 2007 10:51:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Bernt! Committed revision 495543.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12464222" author="djd" created="Fri, 12 Jan 2007 15:38:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I can confirm that adding ibmjcefw.jar to the java14compile.classpath with IBM 1.4.2 is required and works.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m confused as to why though explicit adding of JCE libraries is required since I thought from 1.4 onwards they are part of the standard JDK.&lt;br/&gt;
Is it something to do with how Derby&apos;s javac target is set up?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12464321" author="knutanders" created="Fri, 12 Jan 2007 19:45:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think jce.jar is required because Derby is compiled with bootclasspath set to tools/java/empty.jar.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12467039" author="bernt" created="Wed, 24 Jan 2007 13:32:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Verified and ok.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
